INSERT INTO `wp_options` VALUES("586", "_transient_6dcf381699fcd050c8eaf782f6513d46", "<h1 class=\"title\"></h1><div class=\"container\"><div class=\"post-content\">\n                <div class=\"row\">\n\n                <div class=\"col-sm-10 post-content col-sm-offset-1\"><p><img style=\"width: 50%;\" src=\"http://d7j863fr5jhrr.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/wordpress-how-to-create-magazine-site.png\" alt=\"How to create a magazine site with WordPress\" width=\"469\" height=\"290\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-280178\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Custom content lets you enhance your blog.</strong> You will be able to design a magazine-style homepage, and customize the content of posts. Types plugin will allow you to add custom posts and fields to the WordPress admin. Here, the same rules apply as introduced in <a href=\"https://wp-types.com/how-to/develop-brochure-site-wordpress/\">‘Building brochure sites’</a> documentation.</p>\n<p class=\"clearfix\">To display custom content on the site’s front-end, you can either edit the PHP templates of your theme, or use <a href=\"https://wp-types.com/home/views-create-elegant-displays-for-your-content/\">Views</a> plugin. Views lets you customize the appearance of your blog without writing PHP.</p>\n<h2>Displaying Custom Content on the Site’s Front-end</h2>\n<table class=\"table spaced-table\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 30%;\">What you will need</th>\n<th style=\"width: 30%;\">How to achieve it in WordPress</th>\n<th style=\"width: 30%;\">How to do it with Views</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Customize your archive pages and display fields that you chose.</strong></p>\n<p><img src=\"http://d7j863fr5jhrr.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/wordpress-blog-archive-page.png\" alt=\"WordPress archive customization\" width=\"270\" height=\"341\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-280920\" /></p>\n<figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">WordPress archive customization</figcaption>\n</td>\n<td>Edit a relevant archive template:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>home.php/index.php</li>\n<li>author archive</li>\n<li>category archive</li>\n<li>cust post archive</li>\n<li>etc.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Use WordPress API and PHP to display your post data, e.g:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the_title() for post title</li>\n<li>the_content for post body</li>\n<li>the_post_thumbnail for feature image</li>\n<li>the_author() for author</li>\n<li>etc</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td>Create a new WordPress Archive with Views plugin and edit it like you edit WordPress pages. Insert the fields that you need from a GUI and style the output using HTML tags.\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Create custom magazine layouts</strong></p>\n<p><img src=\"http://d7j863fr5jhrr.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/wordpress-homepage.jpg\" alt=\"A homepage that includes a slider with recent products, featured services, and recent articles.\" width=\"270\" height=\"264\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-280895\" /></p>\n<figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">Homepage with a magazine layout</figcaption>\n</td>\n<td>Create or edit home.php template of your theme and add custom WP queries for each section.</td>\n<td>Create a <a href=\"https://wp-types.com/documentation/user-guides/normal-vs-archive-views/\">WordPress Archive</a> for the homepage. Then, create Views for each of the sections. Finally, insert the Views into the the WordPress Archive.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Create custom widgets.</strong></p>\n<p><img src=\"http://d7j863fr5jhrr.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/latest-news-widget.jpg\" alt=\"Latest posts with featured images\" width=\"270\" height=\"355\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-280921\" /></p>\n<figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">Latest posts with featured images</figcaption>\n</td>\n<td>Create custom widgets coded with widgets API, WP_query and PHP.</td>\n<td>Create a View, select it to display Posts. Include ‘Featured image’, ‘Excerpt’ and post URL shortcodes in your output. Include this View in a WP Views widget &#8211; a dedicated widget allowing to display any View.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Display related custom content inside blog posts:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>advertisements</li>\n<li>related recipes</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"http://d7j863fr5jhrr.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/related-posts-wp.jpg\" alt=\"Related posts with featured images\" width=\"270\" height=\"132\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-280922\" /></p>\n<figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">Related posts with featured images</figcaption>\n</td>\n<td>Edit a single.php file to add custom php code: get the current post categories, query posts that belong to these categories, loop through the results to display posts; titles and links.</td>\n<td>Create a View, select it to display Posts. Add a Query Filter by category, and set it to: ‘Taxonomy is: Value set by current page’. Include ‘Title with link’ in your output to show related posts. Use this View in a single post <a href=\"https://wp-types.com/documentation/user-guides/view-templates/\">Content Template</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2 id=\"examples\">Examples of News-Magazine like Sites Built with Toolset</h2>\n<div class=\"well well-default \"></p>\n<p>Want to get inspiration ideas from others? Look at some examples of news-magazine like sites built with <a href=\"http://wp-types.com\">Toolset</a> plugins.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://ref.wp-types.com/bootmag/\">ref.wp-types.com/bootmag </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.techinside.com/\">www.techinside.com</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.laagendacultural.cl/\">www.laagendacultural.cl</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p></div>\n</div></div></div>                ", "no");
